This paper deals with natural language processing and machine translation, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves measuring perplexity, which is a common evaluation metric in neural machine translation, and this falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper includes a study on paraphrase generation, which could potentially involve computer vision techniques, and this falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
